It was outside a Mayfair school more than a month ago where an 11-year-old girl was snatched. She was kidnapped by two men with rifles. After an extensive police investigation, by Crime Intelligence's Kidnapping Task Team, she has been rescued. eNCA's Barry Bateman fills us in. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The newly-established Crime Intelligence Kidnapping Task Team has made another breakthrough. The 11-year-old girl snatched outside her school in Mayfair in November has been rescued. READ: Girl kidnapped outside Mayfair primary school found However, no suspects have been arrested at this stage. The child's father has thanked the public for the outpouring of support but says they aren’t prepared to speak publicly at this stage. READ: Mayfair kidnapping | Gauteng Education to provide support The Gauteng Education Department says they will provide all the necessary support to the girl and her family. * eNCA's Barry Bateman reports.